#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "**USAGE_2D_NO_SAMPLING** = **1** --- Allocates"
#~ " buffers needed for 2D scenes without"
#~ " allocating a buffer for screen copy."
#~ " Accordingly, you cannot read from "
#~ "the screen. Of the :ref:`Usage "
#~ "<enum_Viewport_Usage>` types, this requires "
#~ "the least VRAM."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "**USAGE_3D** = **2** --- Allocates full"
#~ " buffers for drawing 3D scenes and"
#~ " all 3D effects including buffers "
#~ "needed for 2D scenes and effects."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "**USAGE_3D_NO_EFFECTS** = **3** --- Allocates"
#~ " buffers needed for drawing 3D "
#~ "scenes. But does not allocate buffers"
#~ " needed for reading from the screen"
#~ " and post-processing effects. Saves "
#~ "some VRAM."
